WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:04.220
In the Game of Thrones books, there are lots
of characters that don’t appear in the TV

00:00:04.220 --> 00:00:10.009
show – like the rogue maester Marwyn, and
the wildling princess Val. One of the weirdest

00:00:10.009 --> 00:00:17.140
of these book characters is Patchface. Patchface
is a jester serving Stannis Baratheon at Dragonstone.

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:21.970
He hangs out with Stannis’ daughter Shireen
and sings strange songs about shadows and

00:00:21.970 --> 00:00:27.130
the sea. He seems to be a sort of prophet
of the Drowned God. But he’s also connected

00:00:27.130 --> 00:00:32.500
to the white walkers, the Lovecraftian Deep
Ones, and greyscale.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:37.760
So about twenty years ago, in the castle of
Storm’s End, there lived Steffon Baratheon,

00:00:37.760 --> 00:00:43.530
his wife Cassana, and their young sons Robert,
Stannis, and Renly. The king, Aerys Targaryen,

00:00:43.530 --> 00:00:48.290
sent Steffon across the narrow sea to find
a wife for Prince Rhaegar . Steffon didn’t

00:00:48.290 --> 00:00:53.820
find a likely bride, but he did he find a
remarkable young slave boy – his face tattooed

00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:58.870
with “red and green motley” . The boy
was smart and nimble, could juggle and joke,

00:00:58.870 --> 00:01:03.860
and sing in four different languages. So Steffon
decided to bring the boy home for his family

00:01:03.860 --> 00:01:09.119
. But on the way back, Steffon’s ship was
smashed in a storm – Steffon, Cassana, and

00:01:09.119 --> 00:01:15.420
a hundred men were drowned . Corpses washed
up at Storm’s End for days afterward. And

00:01:15.420 --> 00:01:21.609
on the third day, Patchface washed up – naked,
sandy and cold. He seemed dead, but then woke

00:01:21.609 --> 00:01:27.079
up, alive , though he was “broken in body
and mind”. Patchface was no longer bright

00:01:27.079 --> 00:01:32.640
and clever – he now seemed “mad”, talking
nonsense, twitching and trembling . Some wanted

00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:37.640
to put Patchface out of his misery – Maester
Cressen spared his life, but doubts if Patchface

00:01:37.640 --> 00:01:43.780
is even glad to be alive . By Book 2, Patchface
lives on Dragonstone with Shireen. She’s

00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:48.649
a sad, lonely girl , and she forms a sweet
friendship with Patchface , who she calls

00:01:48.649 --> 00:01:54.789
Patches. They keep each other company on bleak
grey Dragonstone. But there is a creepiness

00:01:54.789 --> 00:02:00.639
and a darkness to Patchface.
Patchface doesn’t talk normally. He just

00:02:00.639 --> 00:02:05.490
has these weird songs and rhymes about the
world “under the sea” – about fish,

00:02:05.490 --> 00:02:10.330
and mermaids, and shadows. He speaks about
“under the sea” as like an opposite-world

00:02:10.330 --> 00:02:15.450
to the world on land, like “Here we eat
fish”, but “Under the sea, the fish eat

00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:20.080
us” . He falls down to the ground, then
says “Under the sea, you fall up” , which

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:26.320
might refer to how corpses float – the sea
seems connected to death in his songs. Some

00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:32.290
of Patches’ songs don’t mean much in particular.
But others predict future events. In Book

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:36.620
3, he sings “Fool’s blood, king’s blood,
blood on the maiden’s thigh, but chains

00:02:36.620 --> 00:02:41.909
for the guests and chains for the bridegroom,
aye aye aye” . This describes the Red Wedding

00:02:41.909 --> 00:02:46.700
– the “Fool’s blood” is Aegon Frey’s
– who doesn’t appear in the show – the

00:02:46.700 --> 00:02:50.190
“king’s blood” is Robb Stark’s, the
“blood on the maiden’s thigh” is from

00:02:50.190 --> 00:02:54.570
Roslin Frey losing her virginity, and the
chains for the guests and bridegroom refer

00:02:54.570 --> 00:03:00.000
to Edmure and other imprisoned survivors.
So this is an accurate prediction of the future

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.730
by Patchface – and there are others. Like,
Patchface says “under the sea” “The

00:03:04.730 --> 00:03:10.330
merwives wear nennymoans in their hair and
weave gowns of silver seaweed” . At Joffrey’s

00:03:10.330 --> 00:03:15.730
wedding, Sansa wears a silver gown in the
books , and in her hair is hidden the poison

00:03:15.730 --> 00:03:21.370
that Olenna uses to kill Joffrey . So maybe
this is Patchface’s vision of Joffrey’s

00:03:21.370 --> 00:03:27.100
death. In a Davos chapter, Patches sings “Under
the sea, smoke rises in bubbles, and flames

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:31.810
burn green and blue and black” . This might
be a warning for Davos about the Battle of

00:03:31.810 --> 00:03:37.850
the Blackwater, where green wildfire burns
amidst black smoke and blue sea .

00:03:37.850 --> 00:03:42.771
Another song that Patchface often sings goes
“The shadows come to dance”, “The shadows

00:03:42.771 --> 00:03:48.090
come to stay” . This might refer to the
shadow monsters Melisandre uses to kill people

00:03:48.090 --> 00:03:52.740
. But it might also refer to the white walkers
– who are described as “shadows” in

00:03:52.740 --> 00:03:58.440
the books . Patchface also refers to the walkers’
army of the dead – “In the dark the dead

00:03:58.440 --> 00:04:04.480
are dancing” he sings . So how does Patchface
know these things about darkness and death,

00:04:04.480 --> 00:04:10.940
and the sea, and the future? He seems to be
connected to the power of the Drowned God.

00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:16.360
It’s a mystery how Patchface survived a
shipwreck that killed everyone else on-board.

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:21.619
We’re told “No one ever explained those
two days the fool had been lost in the sea”

00:04:21.619 --> 00:04:26.090
. And when Patchface washed up, his flesh
was “cold” – he seemed dead until he

00:04:26.090 --> 00:04:31.030
“coughed water and sat up” . This kind
of revival after drowning is similar to the

00:04:31.030 --> 00:04:35.460
drowning ritual of the ironborn. Believers
of the Drowned God are deliberately drowned

00:04:35.460 --> 00:04:40.020
then revived as a show of faith . Patchface
lives on the opposite side of Westeros to

00:04:40.020 --> 00:04:45.280
the ironborn, but still, his songs closely
connect with their religion. Like, ironborn

00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:49.219
believe that after they die, they’ll go
to “the Drowned God’s watery halls”

00:04:49.219 --> 00:04:53.800
to “feast” with “mermaids” “for
all eternity” – like a Bikini Bottom version

00:04:53.800 --> 00:04:59.249
of Valhalla. And in Patchface’s songs, he
describes feasting with mermen under the sea

00:04:59.249 --> 00:05:04.780
. He even mentions mermaids blowing seashells
like trumpets , and Asha Greyjoy says the

00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:09.419
same thing – that merlings blow seashells
in “the Drowned God’s watery halls”

00:05:09.419 --> 00:05:14.200
. So Patchface seems to know an awful lot
about the underwater afterlife of the Drowned

00:05:14.200 --> 00:05:19.160
God. He’s constantly talking about the world
“under the sea”. And his revival after

00:05:19.160 --> 00:05:24.660
drowning is similar to the ironborn ritual.
So there seems to be some connection between

00:05:24.660 --> 00:05:30.479
Patchface and the Drowned God. The popular
theory is that Patchface died in this shipwreck.

00:05:30.479 --> 00:05:35.650
He drowned, and sank into the watery halls,
then was resurrected by the Drowned God to

00:05:35.650 --> 00:05:41.960
be his prophet.
All the cool hip gods have undead human champions

00:05:41.960 --> 00:05:47.349
. Beric Dondarrion is resurrected by the magic
of the fire god R’hllor . Bloodraven and

00:05:47.349 --> 00:05:53.150
Coldhands serve the old gods . White walkers
raise wights apparently to serve their god

00:05:53.150 --> 00:05:58.870
“the Great Other” . So we got ice zombies,
fire zombie, old gods nature zombies – maybe

00:05:58.870 --> 00:06:05.040
Patchface is a water zombie, raised to serve
the Drowned God. The book character Aeron

00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:09.960
Greyjoy, or Damphair, believes himself to
be the prophet of the Drowned God. He claims

00:06:09.960 --> 00:06:15.199
to have died and seen the watery halls, then
been resurrected . But Damphair’s never

00:06:15.199 --> 00:06:21.139
made a prophecy, or done anything particularly
magical. His beliefs seem to be just a coping

00:06:21.139 --> 00:06:26.569
mechanism, to feel powerful after childhood
abuse . But Patchface was drowned and reborn

00:06:26.569 --> 00:06:33.000
for real, and he shows that being the avatar
of a god is way more ugly and dark than Damphair

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:38.960
realises. Look at Bloodraven, Coldhands and
Beric – these are damaged men. To become

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:44.139
something divine, they have to lose part of
their humanity . Beric barely remembers his

00:06:44.139 --> 00:06:49.819
old life , and Bloodraven is more tree than
man . Patchface is the same – the sea has

00:06:49.819 --> 00:06:54.639
taken “half his wits and all his memory”
. He’s gained power as a prophet of the

00:06:54.639 --> 00:07:00.599
Drowned God, but he’s lost who he was before.
So Patchface being the undead champion of

00:07:00.599 --> 00:07:05.800
the Drowned God totally fits the themes of
gods and magic in Game of Thrones. And it

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:11.050
also fits with the logic of sacrifice. We’re
told a bunch of times that “Only death can

00:07:11.050 --> 00:07:16.650
pay for life” – like when Dany’s unborn
child is sacrificed to raise Drogo. A hundred

00:07:16.650 --> 00:07:21.830
Baratheon men drowned along with Patchface,
and the ironborn see drowning people as a

00:07:21.830 --> 00:07:27.129
sacrifice to the Drowned God . So these deaths
might’ve worked as a sacrifice to pay for

00:07:27.129 --> 00:07:32.490
Patchface’s resurrection. It all adds up
– it’s likely that Patchface was resurrected

00:07:32.490 --> 00:07:36.960
to serve as a prophet of the Drowned God.
And it’s through this magic that Patchface

00:07:36.960 --> 00:07:44.139
has insight into the ocean, darkness and death.
But is Patchface warning against the darkness,

00:07:44.139 --> 00:07:49.729
or is he part of it? Melisandre says that
Patchface is “dangerous” – she sees

00:07:49.729 --> 00:07:55.509
him in visions with skulls about him, and
bloody red lips . The red priest Moqorro says

00:07:55.509 --> 00:08:00.889
the Drowned God is a “demon”, a thrall
of the “god” of the white walkers. Does

00:08:00.889 --> 00:08:04.639
this mean that Patchface is on the side of
the dead?

00:08:04.639 --> 00:08:09.800
In Book 5, Jon Snow plans the mission to Hardhome,
where thousands of wildlings are attacked

00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:14.560
by white walkers and their zombies. Someone
asks who’ll lead the mission, and Patchface

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:20.029
says “I will lead it!” “We will march
into the sea and out again” . If the sea

00:08:20.029 --> 00:08:25.069
represents death in Patchface’s songs, marching
into the sea could mean dying – like the

00:08:25.069 --> 00:08:30.120
people killed at Hardhome. But Patchface says
he’ll then march back out of the sea, which

00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:36.060
could mean rising again from death – just
like the zombies raised at Hardhome. Patchface

00:08:36.060 --> 00:08:40.390
also says that “mermaids will blow seashells
to announce our coming” – just like the

00:08:40.390 --> 00:08:44.709
Night’s Watch blows horns to announce the
coming of white walker attacks . So these

00:08:44.709 --> 00:08:49.779
lines do seem to refer to the massacre at
Hardhome, which hasn’t actually happened

00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:54.630
in the books yet – we’ve only just heard
about “Dead things in the woods” and “Dead

00:08:54.630 --> 00:09:00.060
things in the water” . So we don’t know
if Patchface will play a role here. But whatever

00:09:00.060 --> 00:09:05.590
happens at Hardhome, it’s telling that Patchface
uses these words “we” and “our”. It

00:09:05.590 --> 00:09:12.070
sounds like Patchface is on the side of the
dead – just as Mel and Moqorro warn.

00:09:12.070 --> 00:09:17.589
And there is another kind of evil connected
to Patchface – the Deep Ones. Author George

00:09:17.589 --> 00:09:23.820
Martin is a fan of H. P. Lovecraft, who wrote
stories about the cosmic horror of alien gods.

00:09:23.820 --> 00:09:28.350
There are lots of references to Lovecraft
in Game of Thrones, like these ancient ruined

00:09:28.350 --> 00:09:34.420
cities in the east – K’dath , Carcosa,
Leng . One Lovecraft story, called The Shadow

00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:40.350
over Innsmouth, is about the Deep Ones, fishy
creatures that breed with humans. And there

00:09:40.350 --> 00:09:44.860
are hints that these creatures exist in Game
of Thrones . We hear about “squishers”,

00:09:44.860 --> 00:09:49.610
half-fish creatures who breed with humans
. And we see families in Westeros with webbed

00:09:49.610 --> 00:09:55.220
fingers and bulging eyes , just like the half-fish
hybrids in the Lovecraft story. It’s said

00:09:55.220 --> 00:10:00.910
that the Deep Ones built structures in Westeros,
including the Seastone Chair of the ironborn

00:10:00.910 --> 00:10:06.630
. It’s said that the Drowned God is the
father of the Deep Ones . And this idea of

00:10:06.630 --> 00:10:12.769
fish creatures breeding with humans is connected
to Patchface. After Patches drowned, fisherfolk

00:10:12.769 --> 00:10:18.069
said that “a mermaid had taught [Patchface]
to breathe water in return for his seed”

00:10:18.069 --> 00:10:24.089
. And Patchface says “Under the sea, men
marry fishes … They do, they do, they do”

00:10:24.089 --> 00:10:29.480
. Could Patchface be involved with the Deep
Ones’ plans to breed with humans? This could

00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:35.320
cast a shadow over Patches’ relationship
with Shireen. In Book 5, he takes her by the

00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:41.649
hand and sings “Come with me beneath the
sea, away, away, away” .

00:10:41.649 --> 00:10:47.579
There is another dark possibility for Patchface
and Shireen. When Shireen was a baby, she

00:10:47.579 --> 00:10:52.399
caught greyscale, an infectious disease that
turns the skin grey and hard . It eventually

00:10:52.399 --> 00:10:57.250
covers the body and makes the victim lose
their mind, become a zombielike stone man,

00:10:57.250 --> 00:11:02.579
and eventually die. Children can survive the
infection – and Shireen was one of the lucky

00:11:02.579 --> 00:11:08.060
ones, left just with its mark on her face.
But in Book 5, the wildling Val says that

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:14.320
Shireen is “not clean”. That her greyscale
is just dormant, and will “wake again”

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:19.980
. Could Shireen infect others with deadly
greyscale ? In the show, Shireen is dead,

00:11:19.980 --> 00:11:24.790
burned alive by Melisandre – and nothing
happens with her greyscale. But in the books,

00:11:24.790 --> 00:11:29.569
Shireen’s still alive, and her death might
be different – it could involve greyscale

00:11:29.569 --> 00:11:35.459
and Patchface. Because greyscale is associated
with damp, cold climates . And it’s said

00:11:35.459 --> 00:11:41.139
that greyscale was a curse inflicted by a
Rhoynar Prince called Garin as a sort of water

00:11:41.139 --> 00:11:46.820
magic . Some say that Garin has “risen from
his watery grave” to become the Shrouded

00:11:46.820 --> 00:11:52.399
Lord , a figure who spreads greyscale with
a “grey kiss” . So greyscale’s connected

00:11:52.399 --> 00:11:57.730
with water magic, and is spread by a character
who rose from a “watery grave”. Patchface

00:11:57.730 --> 00:12:03.220
is connected to water magic, and rose from
a watery grave. And remember Mel says she

00:12:03.220 --> 00:12:09.029
sees him with “skulls about him”. So maybe,
if Shireen’s greyscale wakes, Patchface

00:12:09.029 --> 00:12:14.980
will help spread it. Maybe when Mel tries
to burn Patchface’s only friend – he’ll

00:12:14.980 --> 00:12:20.879
get mad and start biting people – thus the
bloody lips – causing the greyscale to spread

00:12:20.879 --> 00:12:27.529
into a plague. This could fulfil Mel’s prophecy
of waking a stone dragon – the stone dragon

00:12:27.529 --> 00:12:32.550
could be greyscale. And this ties back to
Shireen because she has dreams of being eaten

00:12:32.550 --> 00:12:39.250
by stone dragons . So, it’s all pretty vague,
but it could fit. This lonely little girl

00:12:39.250 --> 00:12:45.230
and the sad fool of Dragonstone may not only
horrifically die, but they may unleash a grey

00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:51.100
plague on Westeros .
So there are three main ideas on the fate

00:12:51.100 --> 00:12:57.149
of Patchface, and all of them are awful. Maybe
he’ll march with the army of the dead. Maybe

00:12:57.149 --> 00:13:01.940
he’ll take Shireen to the Deep Ones for
breeding. Maybe Patchface will wake a grey

00:13:01.940 --> 00:13:06.639
plague. It’s all fucked. And that’s what
magic’s like in Game of Thrones. This is

00:13:06.639 --> 00:13:13.089
no swish-and-flick shit, the gods only give
at great terrible cost. And these eldritch

00:13:13.089 --> 00:13:20.399
forces are rising. “Old powers waken. Shadows
stir. An age of wonder and terror will soon

00:13:20.399 --> 00:13:25.949
be upon us” . This is what the Winds of
Winter will bring.

00:13:25.949 --> 00:13:29.649
